---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Hero from "../components/Svelte/Hero.svelte";
import DevTools from "../components/Svelte/DevTools.svelte";
import TodoTools from "../components/Svelte/TodoTools.svelte";
// MathTools is temporarily disabled as it needs to be reworked
// import MathTools from "../components/Svelte/MathTools.svelte";
---

<Layout
  title="Svelte in Astro"
  description="Demonstrating Svelte integration with Astro"
  primaryBallColor="#FF3E00"
  secondaryBallColor="#40B3FF"
>
  <main class="container mx-auto px-4 py-8">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-6 text-center">Svelte + Astro Integration</h1>
    <p class="text-lg mb-8 text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      This page demonstrates how Svelte components can be seamlessly integrated into an Astro project.
      Each component below showcases different aspects of Svelte's capabilities.
    </p>
    
    <div class="card bg-base-200 shadow-xl max-w-4xl mx-auto mb-12">
      <div class="card-body">
        <h2 class="card-title">Svelte Hero Component</h2>
        <Hero client:load />
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 max-w-6xl mx-auto mb-12">
      <div class="card bg-base-200 shadow-xl h-full">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h2 class="card-title">Developer Tools</h2>
          <DevTools client:load />
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="card bg-base-200 shadow-xl h-full">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h2 class="card-title">Todo Application</h2>
          <TodoTools client:load />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="prose max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <h2>Why Svelte with Astro?</h2>
      <p>
        Svelte is a radical new approach to building user interfaces. Whereas traditional frameworks like React and Vue do the bulk of their work in the browser, Svelte shifts that work into a compile step that happens when you build your app.
      </p>
      <p>
        When combined with Astro's partial hydration approach, Svelte components can be selectively hydrated only when needed, resulting in extremely fast page loads and minimal JavaScript sent to the browser.
      </p>
      
      <h2>Key Benefits</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>No Virtual DOM</strong> - Svelte compiles your code to tiny, framework-less vanilla JS</li>
        <li><strong>True reactivity</strong> - No more complex state management libraries</li>
        <li><strong>Less code</strong> - Write less code to achieve the same results as other frameworks</li>
        <li><strong>Built-in animations</strong> - Smooth transitions with minimal effort</li>
        <li><strong>Accessibility</strong> - Built-in accessibility warnings during development</li>
      </ul>
      
      <h2>Getting Started</h2>
      <p>
        To use Svelte in your Astro project:
      </p>
      <ol>
        <li>Install the integration: <code>npm install @astrojs/svelte svelte</code></li>
        <li>Add it to your Astro config: <code>integrations: [svelte()]</code></li>
        <li>Create Svelte components in your project</li>
        <li>Import and use them in your Astro pages with <code>client:load</code>, <code>client:visible</code>, or other directives</li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>